    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>Rootgnaw grubs are the larvae of the Rootgnaw Queen — pale, segmented creatures roughly the size of a forearm, that erupt from the earth in coordinated swarms. While individually fragile, they overwhelm prey through sheer numbers, gnawing with crushing mandibles dripping with venom. Each grub burrows quickly between strikes, making them difficult to pin down. The swarm disappears back into the earth when the Queen is slain.</p>",
